title: E11 Smart Merge Strategies with Automatic Conflict Resolution
feature_slug: e11-smart-merge-strategies
verdict: SUITABLE
suitability_assessment: |
  Defense-in-depth enhancement to E11 conflict prediction with 5 layers:
  1. Pattern analysis (append vs edit) in conflict_predict.go
  2. Auto-merge for append-only patterns in finalize_steps.go
  3. Merge strategy suggestions in conflict_predict.go output
  4. Scout prevention guidance in scout.md reference docs
  5. Hook customization examples (non-blocking, documentation only)

  File decomposition: 4 agents, 4 distinct files, no shared ownership:
  - Agent A: pkg/protocol/conflict_predict.go (pattern detection logic)
  - Agent B: pkg/engine/finalize_steps.go (auto-merge orchestration)
  - Agent C: internal/git/commands.go (git diff analysis primitives)
  - Agent D: implementations/claude-code/prompts/agents/scout.md (prevention docs)

  All interface contracts discoverable from existing codebase:
  - git.DiffUnifiedZero already exists for hunk analysis (lines 646+)
  - ConflictPrediction struct already exists (lines 21-24)
  - PredictConflictsFromReports returns result.Result[ConflictData] (line 35)

  Pre-implementation status (sawtools analyze-suitability):
  - Pattern detection: NOT IMPLEMENTED (E11 only detects file overlap, no pattern analysis)
  - Auto-merge: NOT IMPLEMENTED (E11 blocks on any conflict)
  - Merge suggestions: PARTIAL (E11a documents manual escape hatch, but no automated suggestions)
  - Scout prevention: DONE (Scout already avoids overlapping file ownership via I1)

  Parallelization value: 4 agents, Go build+test ~20s, independent files.
  High coordination value: E11 is a common friction point (checker_test.go pattern).

  Estimated times:
  - Scout phase: ~15 min (complex dependency analysis, git primitives)
  - Agent execution: ~4 agents × ~20 min avg = ~25 min (parallel)
  - Merge & verification: ~5 min
  Total SAW time: ~45 min
  Sequential baseline: ~4 × 25 min = ~100 min
  Time savings: ~55 min (55% faster)
  Recommendation: Clear speedup. Proceed.

