pre_mortem:
  overall_risk: medium
  rows:
    - scenario: Auto-merge produces git conflicts despite append-only detection
      likelihood: low
      impact: high
      mitigation: |
        StepAutoMergeAppendConflicts checks for conflicts after each merge and
        falls back to manual merge (with abort) on any unexpected conflict. Tests
        verify fallback behavior.
    - scenario: Pattern detection false positives (classifies line edits as append-only)
      likelihood: low
      impact: high
      mitigation: |
        GetDiffStats uses git diff --numstat which is accurate for line counts.
        Conservative classification: when in doubt, classify as Manual. Tests verify
        edge cases (binary files, empty diffs).
    - scenario: Cross-repo IMPLs where manifest.Repository is empty
      likelihood: medium
      impact: medium
      mitigation: |
        AnalyzeDiffPattern returns error when repoPath is empty. Caller falls back
        to conservative Manual strategy. Document limitation in E11 protocol section.
    - scenario: Agent C and Agent A have circular dependency (both need git.DiffStats)
      likelihood: low
      impact: low
      mitigation: |
        Agent C creates git.DiffStats first (Wave 1). Agent A consumes it (also Wave 1,
        but independent file). No circular dependency — both are leaf nodes in same wave.
